data.name: label2.Text
data.value: - This game was developed as a project for the Faculty of Information Technologies and Computer Engineering, St. Cyril and Methodius, under the mentorship of prof. Dr. Gjorgji Madzarov and assistant Aleksandar Stojmenski.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: - Understanding the competitive spirit of gamers and the desire for simple games, we decided to create a game that would be simple, but also interesting to play. The goal of the game is to score as many points as possible by hitting the targets.

data.name: label10.Text
data.value: - The player must hit as many targets as possible in the given time period of one minute. When the timer ends, the user is prompted with a dialog of his score and saves his score to the database if his previous high score is beaten.
